You got the calculations right, but haste percent does NOT equal DPS percentage increase.<br>
<br>
EDIT: clarification.<br>
<br>
Increasing haste percent simply adds more swings per unit of time.  For example, given a 40 delay weapon:<br>
<br>
At 0% haste: 15 swings per minute<br>
At 100% haste: 30 swings per minute<br>
<br>
Thus, haste merely grants more possible hits per unit of time.  While in many cases going from 0% haste to 100% haste may double ones DPS, it is not a guarantee in all situations.  Thus a blanket statement like the one quoted above should be worded more carefully.  <p><font face="tahoma" size=-1><b><a href="http://moresoda.com/eq/">Labiara Stankfoot</a><br>
